    • getAccessibleFolderIds

      IDfList getAccessibleFolderIds()
      Returns IDfList of accessible folder ids. This list has the longest sequence of folder ids in a given object path, that are accessible by user, from the bottom up. Sequence of ids in this list corresponds to a value, returned by getAccessiblePath(). For example, if path is “/a/b/c/x/y/z”, and c is not accessible, but x, y, and z are, the return value is a list that has ids of "x", "y", and "z".
      Returns:
      IDfList list of IDfId objects.

    • getAccessiblePath

      String getAccessiblePath()
      Returns user-accessible path. This String has the longest sequence of folder names in a given object path, that are accessible by user, from the bottom up. It starts with "/" only if path is fully accessible. For example, if path is “/a/b/c/x/y/z”, and c is not accessible, but x, y, and z are, the return value is "x/y/z".
      Returns:
      user-accessible path as a String.

    • isPartial

      boolean isPartial()
      Returns:
      true, if path is partial, false otherwise.
